      "side": 1,
      "message": "I wonder whether we might get nicer error messages if that `p.peek()` was a `p.expect(token.Bind)`?\n\nAs this code stands,\n\n```\ntry x 3\n```\n\ngives the error `expected \u0027{\u0027, found \u0027IDENT\u0027 x` because it\u0027s falling back to to the struct form. By contrast,\n\n```\nlet x 3\n```\n\ngives the error `expected \u0027\u003d\u0027, found \u0027INT\u0027 3:`.\n\nIs there a reason why, if we see an ident to start with, that we should allow falling back to the struct form?",
      "revId": "8b9719d22e53631b6e2525754d9a80a736a49058",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
